The cases in Kentucky continue to increase dramatically. The weekly number of new cases reported has persisted, with more than 100 new weekly cases over the past 2 reporting months, this week 101. Now with the number of cases well over 3000, at this rate that number may surpass 3500 by year's end [2018]. It is unclear what methods are being used to try to stem the tide. Kentucky has more cases in 2018 than was reported in the entire USA in 2016. - Mod.LL

